fields.value: Self-Perceptions of Traits (CAPS-PERTRAIT CAPS-PPPERTRA CAPS-FPERTRAI and CAPS-PEER module)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This 12-item scale, originally developed by Norman (1963) and modified by Cheek (1982) was used to obtain self-ratings of traits. Each item comprised adjective pairs that served as anchors for 9-point bipolar rating scales. Prior research (Cheek, 1982, Norman, 1969) indicates that these 12 items form four orthogonal factors: Extroversion (talkative-silent, sociable-reclusive, adventurous-cautious), Agreeableness (good natured-irritable, mild/gentle-headstrong, cooperative-negativistic), Consc ientiousness (responsible-undependable, neat/tidy-careless, perserving-quitting/fickle) and Emotional Stability (calm-anxious, poised/relaxed-tense/nervous, composed-excitable).

In CAPS/86 this unit was also administered in paper and pencil version (PPPERTRA). Also in CAPS/86 the unit was administered to the CAPS respondent's best same-sex friend (FPERTRAI). And, in CAPS/86 the unit was administered to three of the respondent's friends, who rated both themselves and the CAPS respondent (PEER). NOSA = No standard scoring.
